NandGame:Levels:ASSEMBLER_NETWORK_RECEIV.code:
DEFINE screen 0x4000
DEFINE screenWidthWord 32
DEFINE networkInterface 0x6001
INIT_STACK

# version 2
DEFINE lastSync 10
DEFINE word 11
DEFINE currentScreen 12
DEFINE newSync 13
DEFINE newBit 14
DEFINE i 15

# lastSync = 0
A = lastSync
*A = 0
# currentScreen = screen
A = screen
D = A
A = currentScreen
*A = D

LABEL skipFrameBegin
    # wait for "frame begins" (1)
    # newBit = waitSynedBit()
    PUSH_VALUE onNewBit1
    GOTO waitSynedBit
    LABEL onNewBit1
    # if newBit != 1 then retry the whole frame
    PUSH_STATIC newBit
    PUSH_VALUE 1
    EQ
    NOT
    IF_GOTO skipFrameBegin

LABEL main
    # word = loadWord()
    PUSH_VALUE onNewWord1
    GOTO loadWord
    LABEL onNewWord1
    # *currentScreen = word
    A = word
    D = *A
    A = currentScreen
    A = *A
    *A = D
    # currentScreen += screenWidthWord
    PUSH_STATIC currentScreen
    PUSH_VALUE screenWidthWord
    ADD
    POP_STATIC currentScreen
    GOTO main

LABEL loadWord
    # word = 0
    A = word
    *A = 0
    # for i in range(16)
    # i = 0
    A = i
    *A = 0
    LABEL wordLoop
        # newBit = waitSynedBit()
        PUSH_VALUE onNewBit2
        GOTO waitSynedBit
        LABEL onNewBit2
        # word = word * 2 + newBit
        A = word
        D, A = *A
        D = D + A
        A = newBit
        A = *A
        D = D + A
        A = word
        *A = D
        # i++
        A = i
        D, *A = *A + 1
        # if i != 16 goto wordLoop
        A = 16
        D = D - A
        A = wordLoop
        D; JNE
    # 16 bits loaded
    # skip control bit
    PUSH_VALUE onNewBit3
    GOTO waitSynedBit
    LABEL onNewBit3
POP_A
JMP

LABEL waitSynedBit
    # newSync = network() & 0b10
    A = networkInterface
    D = *A
    A = 0b10
    D = D & A
    A = newSync
    *A = D
    PUSH_D
    # if oldSync == newSync then again
    PUSH_STATIC lastSync
    EQ
    IF_GOTO waitSynedBit
    # oldSync = newSync
    A = newSync
    D = *A
    A = lastSync
    *A = D
    # newBit = network() & 0b10
    A = networkInterface
    D = *A
    A = 0b1
    D = D & A
    A = newBit
    *A = D
POP_A
JMP

NandGame:Levels:CALL.code:
# +1 arg count
PUSH_STATIC ARGS

# +2 local
PUSH_STATIC LOCALS

# +3 ret
PUSH_VALUE afterJmp

# ARGS = SP - argCount - 3(because we just pushed three values on the stack)
PUSH_STATIC SP
PUSH_VALUE argumentCount
PUSH_VALUE 3
ADD
SUB
POP_STATIC ARGS

# call
GOTO functionName

LABEL afterJmp

# store ARGS into temp slot
PUSH_STATIC ARGS
POP_STATIC ARGS_TMP

# restore LOCALS
POP_STATIC LOCALS

# restore ARGS
POP_STATIC ARGS

# restore SP
PUSH_STATIC ARGS_TMP
POP_STATIC SP

# push RETVAL
PUSH_STATIC RETVAL

NandGame:Levels:STACK_EQ.code:

POP_A

# if D == A then D = 0; D = D - 1
# else D = 1; D = D - 1
D = A - D
A = eq
D; JEQ
D = 1

LABEL eq

# save
D = D - 1
PUSH_D

NandGame:Levels:ASSEMBLER_DISPLAY.code:
# for i in range(0x4000, 0x4000 + 512/16*16)
A = 0x4000
D = A
A = 0
*A = D

LABEL loop
# i
A = 0
D = *A
# if i >= 0x4000 + 8192 goto end
A = 0x4200
D = D - A
A = end
D; JGE

# d = 0xffff
D = -1

# *a = pattern
A = 0
A = *A
*A = D

# i += 32
A = 0
D = *A
A = 32
D = D + A
A = 0
*A = D

# goto loop
A = loop
JMP

LABEL end

NandGame:Levels:ESCAPE.code:
LABEL wait
A = 0x7FFF
D = *A
# if turning or forwarding
A = 0b11000000000
D = D & A
A = wait
D; JNE
# reset to op = non
A = 0x7FFF
*A = 0
A = main
JMP

LABEL main
A = 0x7FFF
D = *A
# if obstacle then turn left else forward
A = 0b00100000000
D = D & A
A = left
D; JNE

LABEL foward
A = 0b100
D = A
A = 0x7FFF
*A = D
A = wait
JMP

LABEL left
A = 0b1000
D = A
A = 0x7FFF
*A = D
A = wait
JMP
